# VDR Lifecycle

## Upload Model

- User uploads a ZIP file
- ZIP contains full VDR folder hierarchy
- VDR may contain nested folders/subfolders
- Uploaded ZIP represents a complete snapshot

## Replacement Behavior

Each ZIP upload:
- completely replaces the prior indexed VDR
- clears prior retrieval state
- activates a fresh searchable dataset

No accumulation of old files.

---

# Supported File Types

Primary supported types:
- PDF
- DOCX
- PPTX
- XLSX

Other file types may exist in the ZIP.

Behavior for unsupported files:
- skip gracefully
- never break ingestion
- report unsupported files transparently

---

# Ingestion Requirements

## Required Behaviors

The ingestion pipeline must:
- unpack ZIP files
- preserve full folder hierarchy
- parse supported document types
- extract searchable content
- extract tables where reasonably possible
- preserve metadata
- generate ingestion report

## Graceful Degradation

The ingestion system must:
- continue processing when individual files fail
- skip corrupted/unreadable documents
- never fail entire ingestion because of one bad file

## Ingestion Reporting

Example report:

Indexed:
- 1,284 files

Skipped:
- 14 unsupported file types
- 3 corrupted PDFs
- 2 password-protected XLSX files

